definition.val: A spatiotemporal region encompassing some part of the life cycle of an organism.
Temporal interval that defines rhesus life from the prenatal stage until late adult stage.
Rhesus life cycle that starts with fertilization and ends at birth.

comments: Embryo develops in 165 days (see http://genomics.senescence.info/species/entry.php?species=Macaca_mulatta).

definition.val: Rhesus developmental stage that covers the period from birth until 3.5 years old, when individuals usually reach sexual maturity.

comments: Rhesus reach sexual maturity by 2007 days of age for male, 1231 days for female (see http://genomics.senescence.info/species/entry.php?species=Macaca_mulatta).

definition.val: Rhesus developmental stage that covers the period from birth until about 9 months old, at which point individuals usually wean.

comments: Age of weaning is 292 days, so close to 9.7 months (see http://genomics.senescence.info/species/entry.php?species=Macaca_mulatta).

definition.val: Nursing stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 1 and under 2 months old.
Nursing stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 2 and under 3 months old.
Nursing stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 3 and under 4 months old.
Nursing stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 4 and under 5 months old.

Nursing stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 6 and under 7 months old.
Nursing stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 7 and under 8 months old.
Nursing stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 8 and under 9 months old.
Nursing stage that refers to a nursing rhesus who is over 9 and under 10 months old.

comments: Age of weaning is 292 days, so close to 9.7 months (see http://genomics.senescence.info/species/entry.php?species=Macaca_mulatta). We consider a 9-month-old nursing stage and 9-month-old weaning stage.

definition.val: Rhesus developmental stage that covers the period from about 9 months old, when individuals usually wean, until 3.5 years old, when individuals usually reach sexual maturity.

comments: This stage starts at 9.7 months, the usually weaning age. We consider a 9-month-old nursing stage and 9-month-old weaning stage. Rhesus reach sexual maturity by 2007 days of age for male, 1231 days for female (see http://genomics.senescence.info/species/entry.php?species=Macaca_mulatta).

definition.val: Juvenile stage stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 9 and under 10 months old.

comments: During this period, juvenile rhesus usually wean (see http://genomics.senescence.info/species/entry.php?species=Macaca_mulatta).

definition.val: Juvenile stage stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 10 and under 11 months old.
Juvenile stage stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 11 and under 12 months old.
Juvenile stage stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 1 and under 2 years old.
Juvenile stage stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 2 and under 3 years old.
Juvenile stage stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 3 and under 4 years old.

comments: Rhesus reach sexual maturity at about 3.5 years, so we consider a 3-year-old immature stage and a 3-year-old mature stage.

definition.val: Developmental stage that refers to a sexually mature adult rhesus, which is usually over 3,5 years old.
Mature stage that refers to a rhesus who is over 3 and under 25 years old, the usual upper limit for breeding age.

comments: This stage actually starts at about 3.5 years, the age of sexual maturity. See 3-year-old immature stage and 3-year-old mature stage. The females of this species reach menopause at about the age of 25 (see http://genomics.senescence.info/species/entry.php?species=Macaca_mulatta). We decided to consider this age as the upper limit for adulthood stage, before geriatric age.

definition.val: Adulthood stage stage that refers to a mature rhesus who is over 3 and under 4 years old.

comments: Rhesus reach sexual maturity at about 3.5 years, so we consider a 3-year-old immature stage and a 3-year-old mature stage.
